           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-11">Village of Vāsavapura: Gho Aṁmr̥ata, Gho Khñuṁ, Gho Chpoṅ, Gho Vrahma, Gho Dharrnma, Gho Kaṁvrau, Gho Dralāy, Gho Kañcan, Gho La-au, Gvāl Kanrat, Gvāl Kaṁpañ, Gvāl Putra, an animal keeper, Gvāl Skap, Tai Saṅkāv, Tai Jvik, Tai Kanteṅ accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Kansū, Tai Kaṁphāc, Tai Chpoṅ, Tai Panheṅ, Tai Kañcū, Tai Kaṁvaḥ, Tai Caṁhek, Tai Khtar, Tai Saṁtap, Tai Kan-a, Tai Kanso. Total: 9 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 5 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 14 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied> and a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total: 29.</p>
              <p n="11-26">Village of Val Gāp: Gho Kaṁpit, Gho Kañjā, Gho Thgap, Gho Rājavikrama, Gho Śri Aji, Gho Kanso, Gho Kaṁpan, another Gho Kaṁpit, Gho Laṁvi, Gho Saṁsāra, Gho Kaṁvai, Gvāl Panpoṁ, Gvāl Thgap, Tai Panlas accompanied by a daughter <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied> called Pravāt, Tai Kan-at accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied> and a boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, Tai Vraḥ Nidhiya accompanied by a son <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> called Khñuṁ, Tai Kantr̥p, Tai Sundara, Tai A Rāja, Tai Prabhāvati, Gho Kanrat, Gho Panlas, Gvāl Phnak, Gvāl Kanrat, Gvāl Kañcan, another Gho Kanrat, Tai Utpala accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Pandan accompanied by a son <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> called Kan-añ, Lap Kaṁva, Tai Thgun accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied> and a boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, Lap Kaṁpit. Total: 4 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 5 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 9 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 2 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, 5 boys at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, a girl at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied> and 3 baby girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>.</p>
